params._deadline: LP deadline for the UniswapV2 implementation
params._overrideBorrowAmt: Override amount to borrow from the lending pair, only matters if max LTV is >50% on the lending pair
params._pairedLpAmtMin: Minimum number of pairedLpTkn for LP, slippage
params._pairedLpDesired: Number of pairedLpTkn for the pod to use to add LP for the new position
params._pod: The pod to leverage against for the position
params._podAmount: Amount of pTKN to use to leverage against
params._positionId: The NFT ID of an existing position to add leverage to, or 0 if a new position should be created
params._selfLendingPairPod: Advanced implementation parameter that is a pod to wrap pairedLpTkn into before adding leverage, or address(0) if not applicable
params._slippage: Slippage for the LP execution with 1000 precision (1000 == 100%)

params._userData: Config/info to unpack and extract individual pieces when adding/removing leverage, see addLeverage and removeLeverage

params._pod: The pod to leverage against for the new position
params._recipient: User to receive the position NFT
params._selfLendingPod: Optional self lending pod, use address(0) if not applicable

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._borrowAssetAmt: Amount of borrowed assets to flash loan and use pay back and remove leverage
params._collateralAssetRemoveAmt: Amount of collateral asset to remvoe from the position
params._dexAdapter: Adapter to use to optionally swap pod token into borrow token if not received enough to pay back flash loan
params._pairedAssetAmtMin: Minimum amount of pairedLpTkn to receive on remove LP transaction (slippage)
params._podAmtMin: Minimum amount of pTKN to receive on remove LP transaction (slippage)
params._positionId: The NFT ID for the position
params._userProvidedDebtAmtMax: Amt of borrow token a user will allow to transfer from their wallet to pay back flash loan

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._positionId: The NFT ID for the position
params._recipient: Where the received assets should go
params._token: The token to withdraw assets from

addLeverage(uint256,address,uint256,uint.notice: The ```addLeverage``` function adds leverage to a position (or creates a new one and adds leverage)

callback(bytes).notice: The ```callback``` function can only be called within the addLeverage or removeLeverage workflow,and is called by the flash source implementation used to borrow assets to initiate adding or removing lev

initializePosition(address,address,addre.notice: The ```initializePosition``` function initializes a new position and mints a new position NFT

removeLeverage(uint256,uint256,uint256,u.notice: The ```removeLeverage``` function removes leverage from a position

withdrawAssets(uint256,address,address,u.notice: The ```withdrawAssets``` function allows a position owner to withdraw any assets in the position custodian
